___NOTES___

WireBoard GTM template, initial release.

Architecture:

- Loads https://static.wireboard.io/wireboard.js (WireBoard tracker SDK) and
  https://static.wireboard.io/events.min.js (custom-event helper + dataLayer
  listener) via injectScript. Activates a single tracker named "wb" via the
  SDK's newTracker / trackPageView API, with the publisher carried in a
  custom context (schema: wb:io.wireboard/publisher).
- For the SDK bootstrap to drain the queued newTracker / trackPageView calls,
  the template uses createQueue('WireBoardNamespace') to register the namespace
  before createArgumentsQueue('wireboard', 'wireboard.q') sets up the queue stub.
  Skipping the namespace registration means the SDK never drains the queue.
- dataLayer auto-capture is implemented inside events.min.js (not in this template).
  The "Auto-capture from window.dataLayer" checkbox calls
  window.wireboardEnableDataLayerListener() directly, exposed by events.min.js.
- Publisher inheritance for Custom Event tags goes through wireboardSetPublisher,
  set by the Initialization tag. No need to repeat the publisher on every event.


